Furthermore, among the 4,171 French queries, 70% are used for cross-lingual query similarity training, 10% are used as the development data to determine the relevancy threshold, and 20% are used for testing.
Among the 1,747 suggested queries, 1,407 queries are recognized as relevant to the original ones, hence the accuracy is 80.9%.
Among the 5,000 French queries, 4,171 queries have their translations in the English query log, and are used for CLQS training and testing.
Then CLQS system is used to suggest relevant English queries for them.
